.nh
.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-whatsapp-up - Deploy, start, and provision the WhatsApp bridge


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel whatsapp up [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Deploy, start, and provision the WhatsApp bridge


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--api-key\fP=""
	Admin secret (ADMIN_API_KEY) for the bridge control plane. A strong one is generated if omitted.

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for up

.PP
\fB--image\fP=""
	Override the bridge container image (BRIDGE_IMAGE). Defaults to the image declared by the module source.

.PP
\fB--port\fP=8080
	Host port to publish the bridge on.

.PP
\fB--proxy\fP=""
	Optional egress proxy for the tenant (socks5:// or http(s)://).

.PP
\fB--public-url\fP=""
	Optional public base URL of the bridge, used only for copy-pasteable QR links.

.PP
\fB--source\fP="sunapi386/whatsapp-bridge"
	Module source for the bridge compose: owner/repo[@ref] or a git URL. The default (sunapi386/whatsapp-bridge) is a PRIVATE repo, so this node needs git credentials (GITHUB_TOKEN or an SSH key) to clone it and a docker login to pull its private image.

.PP
\fB--tenant\fP="default"
	Tenant name (label only).


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel-whatsapp(1)\fP
